# SCSS/BEM Rules

## BEM Naming Convention
- **Block**: Standalone component (`.card`, `.navigation`)
- **Element**: Part of block (`.card__title`, `.card__image`)
- **Modifier**: Variant or state (`.card--featured`, `.card__title--large`)

## Syntax Rules
```scss
// Correct BEM structure
.block {
  &__element {
    // element styles
  }

  &--modifier {
    // modifier styles
  }

  &__element--modifier {
    // element with modifier
  }
}
```

## File Structure (Nuxt 4)
```
app/assets/scss/
├── main.scss              # Entry point, imports all
├── global/
│   ├── _reset.scss
│   ├── _typography.scss
│   ├── _variables.scss    # CSS custom properties only
│   └── _utilities.scss
└── components/
    ├── _button.scss
    ├── _card.scss
    └── _navigation.scss
```

## Conventions
- Use CSS custom properties, NOT SASS variables
- One component per SCSS file
- File naming: kebab-case with underscore prefix (`_user-card.scss`)
- Max nesting depth: 3 levels
- No `!important` unless absolutely necessary

## CSS Custom Properties
```scss
// In global/_variables.scss
:root {
  --color-primary: #007bff;
  --color-secondary: #6c757d;
  --spacing-sm: 0.5rem;
  --spacing-md: 1rem;
  --spacing-lg: 2rem;
  --font-family-base: 'Inter', sans-serif;
}
```

## In Vue Components
- Use `<style lang="scss" scoped>` for component styles
- Import global variables if needed: `@use '@/assets/scss/global/variables' as *;`
- Keep component-specific styles in the component file
- Move reusable styles to `app/assets/scss/components/`
